==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: full-fledged
<hw>full-fledged</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having reached
full development with fully grown adult plumage; ready to fly; -- of a
bird.</def> <contr>fledgling</contr>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fully fledged.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having gained full status; -- of persons in respect
to human roles; <as>as, a <ex>full-fledged</ex> lawyer; by the age of
seventeen I was a full-fledged <ex>atheist</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fully fledged.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Full-formed</ent>⟦br⟧
